.TH DHM 1 "February 2026" "v1.1.0" "DHM User Manual"
.SH NAME
dhm \- Docker Health Monitor, a terminal-based dashboard for Docker.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dhm
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dhm
is a lightweight TUI tool for monitoring Docker containers, 
visualizing dependencies, and tracking real-time resource usage.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display a brief help message and exit.
.SH INTERACTIVE CONTROLS
.TP
.B Arrows
Navigate through the container tree.
.TP
.B Enter
Lock monitoring focus on the selected container (updates Details panel).
.TP
.B I
Toggle between Lite (1s, fast) and Full (3s, CPU/RAM) monitoring modes.
.TP
.B L
View container logs (reversed, with severity highlighting).
.TP
.B R
Restart the selected container.
.TP
.B F1, H
Show the in-app help modal.
.TP
.B ESC, Ctrl+C
Exit the application or close modal windows.
